issue.body:
Anonymous servers are very convenient for testing. They still require
shutdown, but do not require a unique name.

Note that InProcessInternalServer is just a rename of InProcessServer.

The API presented in up for debate. Usage would look like:

```
InProcessServer server = InProcessServerBuilder.newAnonymous().build().start();
ManagedChannel channel = server.newChannelBuilder().build();
```

The main alternative I considered is to add a ServerImpl.getInternalServer() method for the channel builder to use:

```
Server server = InProcessServerBuilder.newAnonymous().build().start();
// Throws if Server is not in-process. Note that no "cloning" is going on
ManagedChannel channel = ManagedChannelBuilder.forServer(server).build();
```

